# Progress reporting

When the user stops, pauses, or the session is interrupted during a multi-step
workload:

- Always include a short progress summary with percentage estimates.
- Cover at minimum: current workload progress, overall migration/plan progress.
- If the session involved orchestrator runs, mention which run is active and
  what the next step would be.
- Keep it brief (3-6 lines max) unless the user asks for more detail.

Example:

> Current workload: ~60%
> Plan 16 overall: ~85%
> Next step: extract v0-fallback stream adapter
